C++ based item modifier generator a la Borderlands or Terraria, creates statistical and behavioural modifiers for items in an RPG style. Can be used in anything from a Turn-Based RPG to shooter with RPG elements context.

How to:

Currently generates plain text output, can be ran in anything that can compile C++, when ran, you are prompted whether to use the default list of items or input your own, 
so far, there are two categories of items, equipables and weapons.
It can run in a GitHub codespace.

Parameters:

There are three parameters that may be adjusted, with comments in the code.
Modifier strength, 1, 2 or 3, determines the strength of both positive and negative modifiers (numerical values).
Wildcard chance, the chance for a special effect of weapon behaviour in percent
Finally, rarity bias, the good or bad bias of modifiers ranging from -100 to 100

Limitations:

This generator is fairly simple and static in quality, 
the items generated by this generator are powerful in an RPG game context, from turn based RPG to an FPS with RPG elements. 
However, this generator is designed with having base items to work on, and complex synergies between items are out of the scope of the generator.
I am also not planning to add nested prefixes, or suffixes as this would convolute it and likely have undesirable side effects.

